  "texts": [
    "For example: The atmosphere of academia and enigma seemed to hang in the air; the air was filled with a sense of togetherness and belonging.",
    "Like a human author, ChatGPT uses idioms and common language reversals in the generated descriptions and dialogues: atmosphere that sends shivers down their spines; a place where the characters' darkest imaginings and deepest anxieties were brought to life; memory modification can be a double-edged sword; guilty as charged; I can't help but feel that…; there's more to this case than meets the eye; someone who would go to great lengths to obtain it.",
    "While generating descriptions, we noticed an interesting detail: ChatGPT uses wooden things description to create an appropriate atmosphere: a wooden staircase that creaks beneath her feet; the floors, made of creaky wooden planks, bore the weight of countless visitors over the years.",
    "These two examples are taken from two different genres of story (Table 1, Story 5 and 3), but they seem to come from the same text and can even be placed in the same paragraph.",
    "It doesn't matter whether ChatGPT is describing a professor's study, an old bookshop or a room of a teenage girl, the result will look similar."
